================================================================================
Third-party dependencies (NOT vendored — installed by the operator)
================================================================================

Tess OS ships ZERO third-party code in this repository. The components below are
external dependencies resolved at install/run time, not copied into the tree.

--- Vault crypto backend (Python `tessctl vault`) ---

  pyrage  (preferred backend)
    Python bindings to the Rust `age`/`rage` implementation. Used by the vault
    to generate X25519 identities and to encrypt/decrypt the local secret store
    in the age armored format.
    License: Apache-2.0 OR MIT (dual-licensed).
    Project: https://github.com/woodruffw/pyrage

  age / rage CLI  (fallback backend — used only if pyrage is absent)
    Tess OS does not bundle the age tool. When pyrage is unavailable it shells
    out to a separately-installed `age`/`age-keygen` (or `rage`/`rage-keygen`)
    binary.
    License: BSD-3-Clause (FiloSottile/age, Filippo Valsorda).
    Project: https://github.com/FiloSottile/age

  PyYAML
    Used by the engine to read tess.lock / tess.manifest.json.
    License: MIT.
    Project: https://pyyaml.org/

--- create-tess scaffolder (npm `npm create tess`) ---

  @clack/prompts
    Interactive prompt primitives for the first-run wizard.
    License: MIT.
    Project: https://github.com/bombshell-dev/clack

  picocolors
    Terminal color output for the wizard.
    License: ISC.
    Project: https://github.com/alexeyraspopov/picocolors
